To upgrade to a newer PDF.js version:
  1. Bump the version pin in this NOTICE and in PanelController.php.
  2. Re-run the SHA-384 + SHA-256 capture:
       curl -sS -fL https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/<NEW>/pdf.min.js \
         | openssl dgst -sha384 -binary | base64 -w0
  3. Update the integrity="sha384-..." attribute in PanelController.php.
  4. Run the panel_controller_pdfjs_smoke.php smoke test (verifies the
     <script> tag carries the expected SHA-384 + the local path resolves
     to a file whose SHA-384 matches).
  5. File a follow-up AgDR if the upgrade involves an API surface change
     in copilot.js (getDocument signature, GlobalWorkerOptions shape, etc.).
